posts.description:
🤦‍♀️ So this week I have:
- Tripped while boxing jumping and face planted in front of the entire gym - Woke up in the middle of the night to buy tights and then got angry the next morning because i was tired, so had chocolate for breakfast - Got overly upset because a mouse ate my last & favourite Easter egg but nothing else in the pantry - Cried on the cross trainer at the gym when I started listening to wedding songs (am I due or what??) - Literally fell over standing up, for no reason, in front of a client - Accidentally set off a mouse trap and almost lost a toe in the process ..... and it's only Wednesday 🙄😂 BUT HEY, 3 days into my 7 day exercise goal and still crushing it. Life goes on peeps, have your cry, eat your choc and get on with it. 👊

This weeks goal: FIND THE TIME. Make sure to do atleast 30 minutes of exercise everyday this week to keep my body moving. Whether it be a walk, run, gym session or HIIT from my living room. I've had a slack couple of weeks (no excuses, I've been SLACK) so this week I'm setting myself a 7 day exercise goal.
It's never about HAVING the time. When you want something bad enough you'll make it happen. So this week, I'm making the time 👊 Who wants to jump on this with me for the week?? Comment below and tag a friend to join in. 🙋✔️

I have a belly full of chocolate but a heart and mind full of motivation for this week 👊 🍫 
My goal: don't eat the rest of the chocolate for breakfast... 🙄 #sendhelp

Making our way home thismorning from a long weekend away and the countdown for the next trip is on.... BALI @activeescapes June 7th 🙏🌴☀️ Give me sunshine and smoothie bowls and fun sweaty workouts with an awesome new group of people 🙌 
If you're already booked to come, I can't wait to meet you and share a whole week with you becoming even more inspired. Pushing our boundaries and comfort zones both mentally and physically, learning new things, eating well, all while having a hellllllll of a lotta fun along the way 😁

YAY FOR LONG WEEKENDS! 🙌 I'm going to give all of you the same lil speech I gave all of my clients this week. 🍫👉 If you want to eat chocolate this Easter, hot cross buns, cake, whatever you want... JUST DO IT. If you don't, don't! No biggie. But don't feel bad about enjoying yourself and ALSO don't be that person that judges the people who do enjoy themselves. 
Each to their own.
One weekend will not completely take you off track of your goals, unless you let it drag on. Indulge, enjoy, live your life, but don't let it spiral out of control. So eat that choc and then after the long weekend you swing your butt into routine and get back on that grind sista ✊️x
Rise & shine fit people 🙌 A new week is waiting for you and you're gonna crush it 👊 Get up, set the goal and get going. X

At least a few times a week I have a different girl say to me "don't give me many weights because I don't want to get bulky"..... 🤦‍♀️ GIRLS. Ya gotta stop this. You won't get 'bulky' unless you want to get 'bulky', unless you eat and specifically train to be that way. What you will get is toned, strong, feminine, lean muscle and less body fat. 
Now hands up who's working with weights today? 🙋 #Me

HEALTH KICK 💥 Stocking up the fridge and pantry for a good week. Aim: more veggies, less processed stuff.
These are my staples that I buy every week, + lean proteins. Oh and some cheeky hidden choc for Sunday night snacking. 🙈🙊
This weeks meal prep looks like:
- Breakfast: berry protein smoothie with almond milk (oats, frozen berries, vanilla protein, vital greens powder)
- Snacks: coconut flakes, almonds, coconut yoghurt/Chobani with Home made granola - Lunch: slow cooked veggies and lean beef in the crockpot with sweet potato.

Be organised! 👊

The difference between those people kicking goals, living the dream and those people who keep missing, isn't always money or luck. 
9 times out of 10 it's showing up when you're tired, pushing through when you don't want to, sacrificing things for a greater purpose, persisting when you get knocked down again and again and again, and above all... bloody hard work. 
You don't need thousands of dollars, it's not who you know or what you know or who can do it for you... its all up to how bad you want it. X

A very un-pretty food photo, BUT, you guys want to see my food! So here it is 😐🤗 My mid morning snack - home made granola and coconut yoghurt. 
I use the Nudie vanilla coconut yoghurt, its bloody amazing and you don't need much. I've started making my own granola to control how much added sugar I'm having everyday. So here's how I make it:
- Mix a couple of cups of whole grain rolled oats with some raw almonds, pumpkin seeds, sunflower seeds, a small amount of raisins/currants and cinnamon.
- Melt some coconut oil, mix through. - Squeeze some natural honey or rice malt, mix through. 
Spread out on a baking tray and bake for about 10 mins, until golden. 😊👌

That new activewear feeling! 😍🙌 It & the motivation that comes with it should be available to everyone! Stoked to share with you guys this new active range from @bigwaustralia 👌 Stylish and super comfy workout gear that really doesn't cost a fortune!! (Finally!) #BigW #LiveBigForLess #BigWActive #BigWFit

Bang! Monday again! 💥 After a very sugary cocktail and cheesey hot dog filled weekend #GirlsNightGotMe🍹🌭 ... I started today with a burning shot of apple cider vinegar, a protein & berry smoothie plus LOADS of water. Feeling better already and so ready to tackle this week! Never sweat the bad stuff, get motivated to do more of the good stuff 👊 #NoRagrets

Been majorly slacking on my yoga and stretching lately, and my body is really feeling it! Flexibility is not where it used to be, range of motion is becoming poor, muscles are becoming tight and achy. So went back to restorative yoga yesterday and it was 🙏🙇‍♀️ I feel so much better already, and now I remember why I love the balance of yoga so much! It's the perfect addition to any routine. More yogi Fridays for me! 🤗

"In three words I can sum up everything I've learnt about life; it goes on"
- Robert Frost

Smiling. Because I'm finally tucked in bed watching TWD with chocolate... because it has been A DAY. Comfort eaters unite 🙄🙋🙌 Who else comfort eats? I feel your pain. It's horrible, give me the food, the struggle is real. But seriously chocolate makes everything feel better. Most days I'll do my best to resist the urge, other days I totally let it take over. But most days, we should remind ourselves of our goals and stay focused. The easiest way to resist a comfort binge is to ask yourself 2 simple questions.
1. Is this going to help me reach my goal?
2. Am I going to regret this later?

Rottweiler ready to pounce on that pre workout 🙈😂 4 PT clients done for the day, 5 to go. Trying to decide between getting my own gym session done first... or having a mid morning nap 🤔 But hey, naps don't get you booty gainz do they. 👊

Breakfasts in Baliiii 🙌🍉🍌 Booked my flights yesterday for @activeescapes in June 👊 Am THAT pumped to spend a week in the sun eating well and training a new group of like minded people. June 7th - a few spots left! Not too late to jump on 👌😊
